<subSubSection id="7BA165330310E113FFCF9993E533FB7E" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FFCF9993E533FB7E" blockId="4.[113,771,1166,1254]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
ETYMOLOGY. The specific name is an indeclinable noun in apposition, taken straight from the Spanish name of the municipalitY from which the 
<typeStatus id="EC00881A0310E113FE1699D3E54BFB7E" box="[424,517,1230,1254]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">holotYpe</typeStatus>
originates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BA165330310E113FFCF9813E639F91E" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FFCF9813E639F91E" blockId="4.[113,771,1294,1670]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
DIAGNOSIS. A medium-sized species (
<quantity id="F4439B5D0310E113FD9B9813E5EBFABE" box="[549,677,1294,1318]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" unit="mm" value="52.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="44.0">44–60 mm</quantity>
) of the “ 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FFC39833E79CFADE" box="[125,210,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">thorellii</emphasis>
” group of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="F4BB4D3B0310E113FE6B9833E52FFADE" authorityName="Marx" authorityYear="1890" box="[469,609,1326,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FE6B9833E52FFADE" box="[469,609,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Centruroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, characterized for the following combination of characters: 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FDE39853E53AFAFE" bold="true" box="[605,628,1358,1382]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">1)</emphasis>
tergites with complete median carinae; 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FE2D9873E6E4FA1E" bold="true" box="[403,426,1390,1414]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">2)</emphasis>
pectinal tooth counts 
<quantity id="F4439B5D0310E113FD1C9873E44DFA1E" box="[674,771,1390,1414]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="3.302" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" unit="in" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15 in</quantity>
both sexes; 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FF499893E643FA3E" bold="true" box="[247,269,1422,1446]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">3)</emphasis>
metasomal segments I-II with strong ventral submedian carinae; 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FEE998B3E623FA5E" bold="true" box="[343,365,1454,1478]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">4)</emphasis>
male carapace 0.91–1.00 times as long as wide; 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FEB498D3E66EFA7E" bold="true" box="[266,288,1486,1510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">5)</emphasis>
carapace with posterior median carinae well developed, granular; 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FEEC98F3E626F99E" bold="true" box="[338,360,1518,1542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">6)</emphasis>
pedipalp chelae with prodorsal carina; 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FFCF9B13E7C6F9BE" bold="true" box="[113,136,1550,1574]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">7)</emphasis>
male telson vesicle elongate, 2.1–2.9 times longer than wide. Its closest relative seems to be 
<taxonomicName id="F4BB4D3B0310E113FDA69B33E54AF9FE" authority="Goodman, Prendini, Francke &amp; Esposito, 2001" authorityName="Goodman, Prendini, Francke &amp; Esposito" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chanae">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FDA69B33E5C7F9DE" box="[536,649,1582,1606]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. chanae</emphasis>
Goodman, Prendini, Francke &amp; Esposito, 2001
</taxonomicName>
; for a comparison, see Goodman et al. (2021b).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BA165330310E113FFCF9BB3E24EFE3A" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FFCF9BB3E5BBF87D" blockId="4.[113,772,1710,2022]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
COMMENTS. Below we will discuss in detail the complete mismatch between the 
<typeStatus id="EC00881A0310E113FEC39BD3E694F97E" box="[381,474,1742,1766]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">holotYpe</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F4BB4D3B0310E113FDB39BD3E5D1F97E" authorityName="Armas" authorityYear="1996" box="[525,671,1742,1766]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmanni">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FDB39BD3E5D1F97E" box="[525,671,1742,1766]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. hoffmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the species identified as such bY Goodman (2021a, 2021b): 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FFCF9A13E65DF8BE" bold="true" box="[113,275,1806,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Color pattern.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="EC00881A0310E113FEF39A13E6E6F8BE" box="[333,424,1806,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">holotYpe</typeStatus>
has the carapace with large and sYmmetrical dark blotches and the tergites with two broad and solid dark longitudinal stripes (see 
<bibRefCitation id="572A4B490310E113FE559A53E5EDF8FE" author="ARMAS" box="[491,675,1870,1894]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="21 - 33" refId="ref2553" refString="ARMAS, L. F. DE. 1996. Presencia de Centruroides schmidti Sissom en el sureste de Mexico Y descripcion de dos especies nuevas (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 36: 21 - 33." type="journal article" year="1996">Armas, 1996: 29</bibRefCitation>
), exactlY as in our specimens conspecific with it (see Martín-Frías et al., 2005: 2, fig. 1). On the other hand, Goodman, Prendini, Francke &amp; Esposito (2021: 68–69, figs. 38–39) depicted the carapace and tergites denselY and irregularlY variegated in the second taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FC8E9DF7E24EFE3A" blockId="4.[816,1475,234,1827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FC8E9DF7E362FE9B" bold="true" box="[816,1068,234,259]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Pectinal tooth counts.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="EC00881A0310E113FBD99DF6E38AFE9B" box="[1127,1220,235,259]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">holotYpe</typeStatus>
has 20/21 (see 
<bibRefCitation id="572A4B490310E113FACA9DF6E4D9FEBB" author="ARMAS" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="21 - 33" refId="ref2553" refString="ARMAS, L. F. DE. 1996. Presencia de Centruroides schmidti Sissom en el sureste de Mexico Y descripcion de dos especies nuevas (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 36: 21 - 33." type="journal article" year="1996">Armas, 1996: 30</bibRefCitation>
), while our conspecific specimens have 
<quantity id="F4439B5D0310E113FAE19C16E28CFEBB" box="[1375,1474,267,291]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.715" metricValueMax="6.096" metricValueMin="5.334" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" unit="in" value="22.5" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="21.0">21–24 in</quantity>
males and 
<quantity id="F4439B5D0310E113FC199C36E349FEDB" box="[935,1031,299,323]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" metricValueMax="5.588" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" unit="in" value="21.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="20.0">20–22 in</quantity>
females, as stated bY Martín-Frías et al. (2005: 5; tab. 3). On the other hand, Goodman et al. (2021b: 48; tab. 8) recorded non-overlapping and much lower counts of 
<quantity id="F4439B5D0310E113FCF39C97E4E2FE3B" box="[845,940,394,419]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="3.302" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" unit="in" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15 in</quantity>
both sexes of the second taxon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BA165330310E113FC8E9CB6E496F8BA" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FC8E9CB6E369FCBB" blockId="4.[816,1475,234,1827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FC8E9CB6E417FE7B" bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Length / width of metasomal segments I / II / III / IV / V.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="EC00881A0310E113FC259CD6E4B4FE7B" box="[923,1018,459,483]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">holotYpe</typeStatus>
female has the following ratios: 1.12 / 1.36 / 1.49 / 1.74 / 2.12 (calculated from 
<bibRefCitation id="572A4B490310E113FABF9CF6E2F3FD9B" author="ARMAS" box="[1281,1469,491,515]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="21 - 33" refId="ref2553" refString="ARMAS, L. F. DE. 1996. Presencia de Centruroides schmidti Sissom en el sureste de Mexico Y descripcion de dos especies nuevas (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 36: 21 - 33." type="journal article" year="1996">Armas, 1996: 28</bibRefCitation>
, tab. 3), because of being immature, slightlY shorter than our conspecific adult females with 1.15–1.23 / 1.40–1.59 / 1.45–1.73 / 1.76–1.95 / 2.14–2.35 (see Martín-Frías et al., 2005: 4, tabs. 1–2, enhanced with our new calculations). On the other hand, Goodman et al. (2021b: 48; tab. 8) gave precise measurements of adult females of the second taxon that allowed us to calculate the following non-overlapping and much longer ratios: 1.28–1.50 / 1.94–2.20 / 2.27–2.40 / 2.34–2.86 / 2.73–3.31.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FC8E9E36E43DFBDA" blockId="4.[816,1475,234,1827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FC8E9E36E485FCDB" bold="true" box="[816,971,811,835]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Telson shape.</emphasis>
Despite being an immature, the 
<typeStatus id="EC00881A0310E113FA869E36E2DBFCDB" box="[1336,1429,811,835]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">holotYpe</typeStatus>
has the vesicle short and bulbose and the subaculear tubercle spiniform (
<bibRefCitation id="572A4B490310E113FC169E76E32CFC1B" author="ARMAS" box="[936,1122,875,899]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="21 - 33" refId="ref2553" refString="ARMAS, L. F. DE. 1996. Presencia de Centruroides schmidti Sissom en el sureste de Mexico Y descripcion de dos especies nuevas (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 36: 21 - 33." type="journal article" year="1996">Armas, 1996: 30</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 8), just like our conspecific specimens (Martín-Frías et al., 2005: 2–3; figs. 5–6, 10; see also Santibáñez-López &amp; Ponce-Saavedra, 2009: 328, fig. 11). On the other hand, Goodman et al. (2021b: 51–52, figs. 24c,f, 25c,f) depicted the vesicle elongate and slender and the subaculear tubercle triangular and compressed in the second taxon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FC8E9956E305FA3B" blockId="4.[816,1475,234,1827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
All differences listed above, as well as others well visible even to unaided eYe, are clearlY shown in the 
<figureCitation id="AB802A3D0310E113FAA69976E23CFB1B" box="[1304,1394,1131,1155]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[113,181,1349,1371]" captionTargetBox="[113,1474,234,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-289@5.[113,1474,234,1342]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Geographical distribution of the authentic Centruroides hoffmanni (circles) and C. concordia sp. n. (triangles), with the tYpe localities indicated in red. Image frame represents 3,800 x 1,550 km (a) and 600 x 245 km (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742187" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742187/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Figure 2</figureCitation>
herein, which includes a topotYpe of the authentic 
<taxonomicName id="F4BB4D3B0310E113FB419996E2C5FB3B" authorityName="Armas" authorityYear="1996" box="[1279,1419,1163,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmanni">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FB419996E2C5FB3B" box="[1279,1419,1163,1187]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. hoffmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the following collecting data: 
<collectingCountry id="4BAC76280310E113FBCC99B6E388FB5B" box="[1138,1222,1195,1219]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="F17FF85A0310E113FB6C99B6E229FB5B" box="[1234,1383,1195,1219]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Chiapas State</collectingRegion>
, Arriaga MunicipalitY, La Gloria Farm, collected inside inhabited house bY public health staff, no date, leg. J. G. Baldazo (
<specimenCount id="25BDFD310310E113FAE699F6E239FA9B" box="[1368,1399,1259,1283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="female">1♀</specimenCount>
RTO). The interested reader will easilY realize its perfect match to the figures published bY 
<bibRefCitation id="572A4B490310E113FBF49836E3A8FADB" author="ARMAS" box="[1098,1254,1323,1347]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="21 - 33" refId="ref2553" refString="ARMAS, L. F. DE. 1996. Presencia de Centruroides schmidti Sissom en el sureste de Mexico Y descripcion de dos especies nuevas (Scorpiones: Buthidae). Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 36: 21 - 33." type="journal article" year="1996">Armas (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, Martín-Frías et al. (2005) and Santibáñez-López &amp; Ponce-Saavedra (2009) on one hand, and its absolute contradiction to those bY Goodman et al. (2021b) on the other.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FC8E98B6E496F8BA" blockId="4.[816,1475,234,1827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
With respect to the infrageneric affiliation of the authentic 
<taxonomicName id="F4BB4D3B0310E113FA1798B6E4EEFA7B" authorityName="Armas" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoffmanni">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FA1798B6E4EEFA7B" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. hoffmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the four diagnostic characters discussed above are enough to demonstrate beYond anY reasonable doubt that it is not a member of the “ 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FB109B16E249F9BB" box="[1198,1287,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">thorellii</emphasis>
” species-group. As first suggested implicitlY bY Martín-Frías et al. (2005) and then formallY established bY 
<bibRefCitation id="572A4B490310E113FB0C9B56E2DEF9FA" author="TERUEL" box="[1202,1424,1610,1635]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" pagination="3 - 14" refId="ref2944" refString="TERUEL, R., F. KOVARIK, J. G. BALDAZO-MONSIVAIS &amp; D. HOFEREK. 2015. A new species of Centruroides of the &quot; nigrovariatus &quot; group (Scorpiones: Buthidae) from southern Mexico. Revista Iberica de Aracnologia, 26: 3 - 14." type="journal article" year="2015">Teruel et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
and followed bY Santibáñez-López &amp; Ponce-Saavedra (2009), it belongs in the “ 
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FBB69B96E3D1F93A" box="[1032,1183,1675,1698]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">nigrovariatus</emphasis>
” species-group, where it is most closelY related to 
<taxonomicName id="F4BB4D3B0310E113FBE39BB6E424F97B" authority="Hoffmann, 1932" authorityName="Hoffmann" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baergi">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FBE39BB6E20FF95B" box="[1117,1345,1707,1731]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Centruroides baergi</emphasis>
Hoffmann, 1932
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4BB4D3B0310E113FCC09BD6E429F89B" authority="Santibanez-Lopez &amp; Contreras-Felix, 2013" authorityName="Santibanez-Lopez &amp; Contreras-Felix" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franckei">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FCC09BD6E34FF97B" box="[894,1025,1739,1763]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. franckei</emphasis>
Santibáñez-López &amp; Contreras-Félix, 2013
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F4BB4D3B0310E113FC209BF6E49AF8BA" authority="Teruel, Kovarik, Baldazo-Monsivais &amp; Hoferek, 2015" authorityName="Teruel, Kovarik, Baldazo-Monsivais &amp; Hoferek" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poncei">
<emphasis id="01CFEAAA0310E113FC209BF6E347F89A" box="[926,1033,1771,1794]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. poncei</emphasis>
Teruel, Kovařík, Baldazo-Monsivais &amp; Hoferek, 2015
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BA165330310E113FC8E9A56E25BF87B" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="330436B80310E113FC8E9A56E252F81B" blockId="4.[816,1474,1867,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">REMARKS. The present description is made in full agreement with Article 13.1.2 of the Code (ICZN, 1999).</paragraph>
